{"word":"H1719 - דְּדָן - Dᵉdân - ded-awn' - Dedan","slug":"H1719","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דְּדָן</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Dᵉdân"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ded-awn'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Dedan"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05D3;&#x05E0;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05D3;&#x05DF; - d<sup>e</sup>da&#x0302;n  deda&#x0302;neh</b> - <i>ded-awn', deh-daw'-neh</i><p/>Of uncertain derivation; <i>Dedan</i>, the name of two Cushites and of their territory. The second form used in <a href='B:330 25:13'>Eze 25:13</a>: - Dedan."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1721\">H1721</a>, <a href=\"#/H7290\">H7290</a>, <a href=\"#/H8639\">H8639</a>"}]}